data.text:
Access Button BOOK YOUR FLIGHT

San Francisco – SFO:

Non-stop flights are available year-round from the Southwest Oregon Regional Airport (OTH). Flights run 7 days a week. Check flight schedules and availability online at www.united.com or call 1-800-864-8331.

Denver – DEN:

United Express offers once-a-day, non-stop flights seasonally on Sundays and Wednesdays to Denver from May to October. Service runs through October 23, 2024.

To book on United call 1-800-864-8331 or visit their website www.united.com

If you need assistance with booking. Contact United or speak to a Skywest Customer Service Representative at the counter located inside the terminal. NOTE: the United/Skywest counter is not always staffed during airport terminal open hours. Email info@flyoth.com for assistance.

Travel advisory: Please arrive at the airport a minimum of 90 minutes prior to the scheduled departure time

Travelers who do not present a REAL ID-compliant license beginning May 7, 2025 will not be permitted through the TSA security checkpoint

Note: Basic Economy travel comes with restrictions for carry-ons. Make sure when you are booking your tickets that you check what is available. A list of Frequently Asked Questions is available here.

TSA will only accept state-issued driver’s licenses if the license was issued by a REAL ID-compliant state in accordance with the REAL ID security standards (meaning the license or card must include the REAL ID-compliant star marking). (Click here for TSA acceptable alternatives to REAL ID)
